name: long-chain-alcohol O-fatty-acyltransferase
classes: Transferring groups other than aminoacyl groups
reaction: acyl-CoA + a long-chain alcohol = CoA + a long-chain ester [RN:R01999]
comment: Transfers saturated or unsaturated acyl residues of chain-length C18 to C20 to long-chain alcohols, forming waxes. The best acceptor is cis-icos-11-en-1-ol.

references.title: Studies of biosynthesis of waxes by developing jojoba seed. 3. Biosynthesis of wax esters from acyl-CoA and long-chain alcohols.
